        <h2>Marina Beach</h2>

        <p>A long stretch of golden sand in Chennai, perfect for a relaxing day by the sea.</p>

        <p>Marina Beach is one of the longest urban beaches in the world, ideal for a peaceful walk or evening outings.</p>

        <!-- Add image for Udaipur -->

        <img src="https://t4.ftcdn.net/jpg/04/84/47/27/360_F_484472702_acpl3SZTBwb2Al4ZiW8VusICp7Utl8ed.jpg" alt="marina-beach-chennai-tn">
       
        <p>
Marina Beach in Chennai is one of the longest urban beaches in the world, stretching over 13 kilometers. Known for its lively atmosphere, it offers a popular spot for walks, picnics, and local street food. The beach is home to landmarks like the MGR Memorial and Vivekananda House. While it’s a hub for relaxation and cultural events, it can get crowded, and cleanliness is occasionally an issue. It remains a favorite destination for locals and tourists alike, especially for morning walks and evening outings.</p>
       
        <h3> REVIEWS :</h3>
       
        <P>Sita :</P>
        <p>I love starting my day at Marina Beach. It’s the perfect place for a morning jog with the sound of the waves and a cool breeze. The view is amazing, and it’s always lively!</p>
       
        <p>Balu :</p>
        <p>There aren’t many proper facilities around the beach, like restrooms or seating. It’s more of a place to walk around and enjoy the view, but not ideal for long stays</p>

